article.headline: In the zone: Cal overpowers Belmont in Vandy tourney
article.linkText: In the zone: Cal overpowers Belmont in Vandy tourney
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Devanei Hampton scored 15 points, and California (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) used its stellar defense to defeat Belmont 69-52 on Friday in the Vanderbilt Thanksgiving tournament.

The bigger, stronger Golden Bears (4-0), playing zone defense nearly all game, held Belmont to 35 percent shooting and forced 20 turnovers.

Belmont (2-2) led early by as many as five, but a 16-0 Cal run midway through the first half broke the game open.

The run began when the Bears, trailing 11-8 at the 12:57 mark, held the Bruins scoreless for the next 5:45. Cal's Lauren Greif helped the run with three defensive rebounds and a steal.

The Bears led 35-22 at the half, and Belmont never got the lead under single digits again.

Belmont's Alysha Clark led the Bruins with 13.

Cal will play No. 14 Vanderbilt (5-0) in Saturday's championship, and Belmont will take on Florida Atlantic (1-5) in the consolation game.
